init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Instead, Earth is populated by a number of different tribes and clans.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: America is therefore a new and exciting place to live, while the rest of the world has become more primitive.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He first had to make sure no one from the outside world could attack America, then he was going to try and open up trade with the rest

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He surrounded America with the military to ensure no one could get in or out, while his government started working with other countries to bring trade back.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was not going to let anyone flood into America and destroy the way of life that had been worked on for the past 50 years.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was going to make sure that those entering the US were from countries that were allied with America and who's people would contribute to the country,
